We think of &quot;infinite&quot; as something that is bigger than what is imaginable (and not imaginable, but that is hard to imagine). For example, we know that we have infinitely many numbers, because we can always add 1.

Now imagine if we have an infinite list of numbers; A={1,2,...-&gt;∞}. Imagine a new infinite list of numbers that is A + 1/2; B={1/2,1,2,...-&gt;∞}

Both A &amp; B is infinite, but B will always have one more number in it (1/2). B is an expansion of A. We have expanded the infinity &quot;A&quot;.

